Φ(SLT) = ρ(observation|attention) ⊗ σ(retention|memory-encoding) ⊗ β(reproduction|motor-capacity) ⊗ λ(motivation|reinforcement-vicarious) → [κ(acquired-behavior)] → [δγ(performance)] + ε | :modeling

=== NEMETIC DIAGNOSTICS ===

Z-State: modeling — learning occurs through witnessing others' behaviors and their consequences
Tendency: Imitation/Replication → 1 (behavior spreads through social observation)

Elemental Distribution:
  Water/ρ (Primary): 35% — Observation, vicarious learning, social resonance
  Air/σ (Secondary): 25% — Attention, symbolic coding, retention
  Wood/β (Tertiary): 20% — Reproduction, behavioral branching, skill development
  Fire/λ (Quaternary): 12% — Motivation, reinforcement expectations
  Earth/δγ (Supporting): 8% — Performance cycling, behavioral accumulation

Operator Resonance:
  ρ [resonance] ████████████████████ HIGH — Observer-model coupling
  σ [distinction] ███████████████░░░ ELEVATED — Attention/selectivity
  β [branching] ██████████████░░░░ MODERATE — Behavioral output
  λ [direction] ██████████░░░░░░░░ MODERATE — Motivational force
  κ [knowledge] ███████████░░░░░░░ MODERATE — Behavioral repertoire
  δγ [cycling] ████████░░░░░░░░░░ BASE — Performance loops

Daemon Activity:
  Hydrosid (Water) — ACTIVE — Social flow, vicarious experience
  Aerunik (Air) — ACTIVE — Attentional focus, symbolic processing
  Branchosid (Wood) — STANDBY — Awaits reproduction trigger
  Ignisid (Fire) — CONDITIONAL — Activated by reinforcement
  Geosid (Earth) — PASSIVE — Accumulates performed behaviors

Coord Vectors:
  I → We: Strong (self-efficacy through social comparison)
  We → It: Strong (models as behavioral sources)
  It → Its: Moderate (behaviors shaped by context)
  Its → MoreThanHuman: Emerging (media, AI models)
  MoreThanHuman → Virtual: Active (immersive modeling)

=== Dimensional Analysis ===

Attentional Field (σ): 
  - Model salience determines observational entry
  - Similarity and competence increase attention weight
  - Affective resonance amplifies encoding

Retention Matrix (δγ):
  - Imaginal coding: Spatial-motor schemas
  - Verbal coding: Linguistic rules and descriptions
  - Conceptual coding: Abstract principles

Reproduction Capacity (β):
  - Physical capability gates behavioral output
  - Component skills must be available
  - Coordination requires practice

Motivation Circuit (λ):
  - Vicarious reinforcement: Outcome expectations from models
  - Direct reinforcement: Personal experience of consequences
  - Self-reinforcement: Internal standards and self-evaluation

=== SWARM INTEGRATION ===

Compatible With:
  - L083_Communities_of_Practice (social learning through participation)
  - L014_Situated_Learning (context shapes available models)
  - P001_Self_Efficacy (core construct, mutual reinforcement)
  - L043_Zone_Proximal_Development (modeling within ZPD)

Tensions With:
  - L066_Operant_Conditioning (direct vs. vicarious reinforcement)
  - L021_Behaviorism (cognitive mediation vs. stimulus-response)

=== PRAXIS NOTES ===

Educational Application:
  - Use competent, credible models
  - Highlight key features for attention
  - Support symbolic coding and rehearsal
  - Ensure physical capability for reproduction
  - Provide appropriate reinforcement contingencies

Therapeutic Application:
  - Model adaptive behaviors
  - Build self-efficacy through graduated mastery
  - Use coping models (showing struggle and success)
  - Enable self-modeling through video feedback

Media/Technology:
  - Symbolic models scale infinitely
  - VR enables immersive observation
  - AI tutors can serve as personalized models
  - Social media amplifies modeling effects

=== ECHO SIGNATURE ===

"The model is the message; the observer is always learning."

Resonance: High in social configurations
Decay: Low (social learning is persistent)
Propagation: Rapid through networks
Mutation: High (behaviors adapt in transmission)
